## Lab 01 – GCP Project Bootstrap & API Enablement

### Why this lab exists
Cloud projects form the security boundary in GCP.
In real environments, infrastructure often fails before deployment
due to project misconfiguration, IAM issues, or missing APIs.

This lab focuses on building a secure GCP foundation using Terraform
and resolving real-world failures encountered during setup.

### What I built
- Terraform provider configured with the correct GCP project ID
- Compute Engine API enablement
- Custom VPC network (no default network)

### Problems encountered
- Terraform failed with Error 403 (SERVICE_DISABLED)
- Project display name was used instead of the actual project ID
- Terraform provider cache required reinitialisation

### Root cause
Terraform was targeting the wrong project identifier,
causing API enablement and network creation to fail.

### Resolution
- Corrected project ID usage in the provider
- Reinitialised Terraform provider
- Ensured APIs were enabled on the correct project

### Outcome
Infrastructure was successfully deployed using Terraform,
with a strong understanding of GCP project-level security boundaries.
